CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 23, 1951, pg. 32 reads: "Carnegie Tech Graduates - Five Negroes received degrees at ceremonies at Carnegie Institute of Technology last Thursday...Elizabeth V. Asche, Beaver Falls, has final touches put on her graduation robe by classmate, Albini Salvatore. Miss Asche was 1950-51 president of Mortar Board, highest senior women's honorary sorority at Carnegie Tech.  She was graduated from the College of Fine Arts....The Courier wishes the [gradu]ates of Carnegie Tech the best of luck in their [vo]cations."
TitMainTitle: Carnegie Tech graduate Albini Salvatore, adjusting collar of Elizabeth V. Asche, standing in Syria Mosque, Oakland
